100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 31, 1925, a significant diplomatic development unfolded as the League of Nations discussed the ongoing tensions in the Middle East, particularly regarding the status of Palestine. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, accused of violating Tennessee's Butler Act by teaching evolution, continued to attract national attention, igniting fierce debates over science and religion. Meanwhile, in Europe, the aftermath of the Ruhr occupation remained a pressing issue, with economic instability affecting Germany's recovery.
